message_1:
Suppose there are 4 factories producing goods and 3 warehouses to which the goods can be transported. Each factory has a certain production rate and each warehouse has a certain demand. The maximum capacity of transportation between any factory and warehouse is given as follows:

Factory 1 can produce 50 units per day;
Factory 2 can produce 60 units per day;
Factory 3 can produce 40 units per day;
Factory 4 can produce 70 units per day;

Warehouse A demands 80 units per day;
Warehouse B demands 50 units per day;
Warehouse C demands 90 units per day.

Determine the maximum number of units that can be transported daily, satisfying the production rates of each factory and the demand of every warehouse.
